about:
A centuryold company that works day to day as the first one

In 1910 the first generation of pastry chefs Jean Cobarsi began his activity in a confectionery workshop in Ceret French Catalonia Its specialties included almond paste nougat pralines candied fruit and longlasting nougats

Years later Cobarsi transferred his Confiserie Roussillonaise as it was called to Santa Coloma Girona Here he expands his range of products and begins to manufacture pastry in bulk Hand in hand with Juan Cubarsí son of Cobarsi and who would be the second generation of pastry chefs in the family they moved to Sant Feliu de Guíxols Girona The range of products continues to grow and they begin to expand the business to the surroundings of the province

Cubarsí Jr begins the construction of a factory in the center of Girona expands the business to the rest of Spain and begins to make a name for itself among the small manufacturers and merchants of sweets and snacks

In 1995 with his son Joan Cubarsí the third generation they constitute a new and modern manufacturing plant and Cubarsí grandson expanded sales to Europe at first and to the rest of the world afterwards until exporting nowadays to more than 40 countries throughout the world

In 2011 the good export climate experienced by the company without ever forgetting the national market led to the acquisition of an 8500m2 warehouse 15 km far from Girona in the town of Bonmatí With a longterm relocation forecast the preparation of the plant begins to adapt it to the needs of a modern industrial pastry factory until 2015 when the desired relocation is carried out

Currently we hope to continue with the good work and with the great human and professional team that is making possible one of the great longings of the Cubarsí family

about:
Cerámicas Aparici representa la más alta calidad de fabricación y diseño innovador La cerámica y el porcelánico premium de esta empresa familiar actúan como una fuerza motriz para los desarrollos y tendencias de toda una industria y están presentes en todo el mundo

El éxito de nuestra marca como fabricantes de azulejos se basa en un principio que se ha mantenido durante más de 50 años el de desarrollar productos que nunca fueran a considerarse como un mero material de construcción sino como un

The success of our manufacturing brand is based on a principle that has held good for more tan fifty years namely that our products should never be regarded as a mere building material but as an essential part of interior and architectural design with the guarantee of their excellent qualitative and aesthetic standards

It was in the 1940s that Maximiano Aparici started producing handmade red bodied bizcocho tiles in a small kiln in the Spanish town of Alcora known since the sixteenth century for its important pottery tradition These tiles were manufactured with the same local red clay that was used back then and that is still used today and then sold on to glazing studios that would apply colour and designs on the unglazed surface

After two decades manufacturing tiles himself in his kiln Maximiano Aparici together with his wife founded Ceramicas Aparici in 1961 The first Ceramicas Aparici factory was his proud accomplishment it was a small factory however it gave him the chance to start manufacturing tiles including the final glazing process that he had been unable to do before using his bicottura or double firing technique

More than fifty years and three generations later Ceramicas Aparici has grown into a company exporting to over 140 countries worldwide and different production plants within the town of Alcora and immediate surroundings  The essence and values of our company have nevertheless remained as those inherited from Maximiano Aparici
keywords: Porcelanc Tiles Tiles Disenus Interior design

about:
Conservera Castreña SA was established in 1986 Our factory is located in the coastal town of CastroUrdiales more specifically in the beautiful valley of Sámano

La Castreña a synonym of quality is our slogan and the principle that has governed our company since the beginning 

The highest quality Anchovy of the Bay of Biscay also known as Cantabrian anchovy scientific name Engraulis encrasicolus is the raw material for our production 

The best anchovies are fished during the spring from April until the end of July when this migratory species approaches the coast It is when its meat is at its best conditions fighting against this wild sea Experienced sailors brave the sea in this time of storms to arrive with the prized silvered cargo to the port

Subsequently comes a handcrafted and centennial process of elaboration in our factory in CastroUrdiales Spain It begins with the headingoff and gutting the selection of the anchovies by its size and continues with the salting process known by the name of Salazón

After maturing in a slow process that lasts for at least 6 months its filleting takes place which consists of the removal of the skin scales and separation of the central bone Then they are packaged and filled with olive oil ready to be offered to the consumer All natural and without artificial additives 

All the processes are controlled by specialized personnel thus getting our brands to enjoy the consumer
Our flagship product is the Cantabrian Anchovies in Olive Oil marketed under the brand name La Castreña in different formats Among our products you can also find Bonito del Norte in Olive Oil and Pickled Ventresca of Bonito del Norte in Olive Oil Cantabrian Anchovies in Vinegar Sardines in Olive Oil etc

Pioneer to incorporate the technology of the rectified in Spain to its ceramic blocks that it markets under the ECOREC brand
What is the rectified technology
The rectified technology consists of a process added to the usual manufacturing process after cooking the support faces of the block are mechanized with abrasive discs until they are perfectly flat and parallel to each other getting a perfect ceramic block and ready for assembly with fine fine joint1mm thick
Ecorec advantages
 Greater energy efficiency reduction of energy consumption is reduced the amount of mortar and water needed to lift the brick walls up to 90 and 95 respectively
 Greater performance in placement The new construction system allows to save up to 40 time in execution with respect to the traditional masonry system
 Better thermal insulation by eliminating the traditional mortar board considerably improves the thermal behavior of the wall by doubling its thermal resistance allowing to save space without reducing benefits
 Improves the mechanical benefits of the factory as there is no need to interrupt the horizontal joint and have a greater grip surface its high mechanical resistance more than 150kg cm2 allows the execution of load walls in buildings of several heights

about:
Tutetecom is dedicated to the sales of personalized soothers and accessories for babies and toddlers

All parents know of the problems which we face when we leave our children at the nursery birthday parties or family gettogethers once we have taken them home we realise thatthey have another childs soother in their mouth Through these means bacteria are passed from child to child which consequently provoke health and hygiene problems

In the majority of nurseries the carers have opted to write the childrens names on their soothers using a permanent marker apart from not looking particularly nice the names will disappear or be erased if the soothers are immersed in hot water and this is even before considering the harm to our children that can be caused by the chemical components of the ink Tired of seeing parents and pedagogues at a loss as to what they could do about the soothers we went to work to find the solution to the problem

After many months of searching and laboratory testing we eventually found what we were looking for  a print which did not erase itself at high temperatures nor through rubbing and which also allowed the little ones to follow the latest trends

So that is how Tutetecom began a company which is concerned with the wellbeing of the our little ones and whose mission it is to offer the latest products of the highest quality which fit the needs of both parents and childcare specialists alike while making their life easier

We develop SaaS solutions to monetize your last mile through time slot deliveries

 Who is our technology for 
For eCommerces that deliver or want to deliver their products in time slots and are looking for an alternative to traditional schedulers

 What problem do we solve
The lack of technology to reliably and affordably deliver products in time slots

 How do we do it 
In your eCommerces checkout we will let you show each customer based on their postal address and cart delivery options in a time slot that will have been prefiltered depending on your delivery resources transportation cost targets and the level of demand for the service you want to offer  These delivery options will result in reliable commitments with your customers and profits for your business
